  "local_port": 43824,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I set a default font in Gmail?",
  "response": "Setting a default font in Gmail allows you to personalize your emails and ensure consistency in your communications. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you set your preferred default font in Gmail using the web interface:\n\n### **1. Access Gmail Settings**\n\n1. **Log in to Gmail**: Open your web browser and navigate to [Gmail](https://mail.google.com). Enter your credentials to sign in.\n\n2. **Open Settings**:\n   - Click on the **gear icon (\u2699\ufe0f)** located in the top right corner of the Gmail interface.\n   - From the dropdown menu, select **\"See all settings\"** to open the full settings page.\n\n### **2. Navigate to the Default Text Style Section**\n\n1. In the **\"Settings\"** page, ensure you are on the **\"General\"** tab. This is usually the default tab that opens.\n\n2. **Scroll Down**: Scroll through the settings until you find the **\"Default text style\"** section.\n\n### **3. Customize Your Default Font**\n\n1. **Set Font Type**:\n   - Click on the **font dropdown menu** to choose your preferred font (e.g., Arial, Times New Roman, Verdana).\n\n2. **Choose Font Size**:\n   - Select your desired font size from the size dropdown (e.g., 10, 11, 12).\n\n3. **Select Text Color**:\n   - Click on the **text color icon (A)** to choose a default color for your email text.\n\n4. **Adjust Formatting** (Optional):\n   - Use the bold, italic, or underline options if you want these styles to be part of your default text.\n\n### **4. Save Your Changes**\n\n1. **Scroll to the Bottom**: After customizing your default text style, scroll down to the very bottom of the **\"General\"** settings page.\n\n2. **Click \"Save Changes\"**: Click the red **\"Save Changes\"** button. Gmail may take a moment to apply your new settings.\n\n### **5. Verify Your Default Font**\n\n1. **Compose a New Email**: Click on the **\"Compose\"** button to draft a new email.\n\n2. **Check the Formatting**: Your new email should reflect the default font settings you configured.\n\n### **Additional Tips**\n\n- **Rich Formatting Toolbar**: If you ever need to change the font for a specific email or section of text, use the rich formatting toolbar at the bottom of the compose window.\n\n- **Reset to Default**: If you wish to revert to Gmail\u2019s original font settings, go back to the **\"Default text style\"** section and select the original options, then save your changes.\n\n- **Mobile App Limitations**: Currently, the Gmail mobile app does not allow you to set a default font. Any changes to font settings must be made using the web interface.\n\n- **Browser Compatibility**: Ensure you\u2019re using a compatible and updated web browser for the best experience with Gmail settings.\n\n### **Troubleshooting**\n\n- **Changes Not Applying**:\n  - Ensure you clicked **\"Save Changes\"** after updating your settings.\n  - Try refreshing your browser or clearing your cache.\n\n- **Formatting Issues**:\n  - If emails appear differently to recipients, it might be due to their email client\u2019s settings. Using standard fonts like Arial or Times New Roman can improve compatibility.\n\nBy following these steps, you can easily set and customize your default font in Gmail, enhancing the appearance of your emails and maintaining consistency in your communication style.",
